    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "html": "/hor nókhôok/ basin owl If you live in Thailand, you can easily find Thai alphabet writing practice books which have pictures showing the meaning of these consonant names to help you create connections between consonant names and the meaning of these names. Use them as writing playgrounds and practise to perfect your Thai characters. Such books are sold everywhere, usually with a BIG picture of a chicken (which is the first letter of the alphabet) on the cover. It’s worth it—get one. Appendix III: Dictionary order Thai alphabetical order in the dictionary is more complex and requires more attention than the English one does. In dictionary order, consonants have priority over vowels. The character order is as follows: CONSONANT SYMBOL ORDER"
    },
